## Core Principles

### 1. Database and external services live in the API app only

All Drizzle queries, Postgres access (via Hyperdrive), and outbound HTTP calls happen in `apps/api`. Clients never touch the database directly.

### 2. All database queries go through Drizzle

Queries live in `apps/api/src/handlers/`, using the Drizzle relational query API. Schema in `apps/api/src/schema/`. Migrations in `apps/api/drizzle/`.

### 3. HTTP-only API access for clients

Public purchase endpoints are Hono routes at `/api/v1/*` with session cookie auth. Handlers are shared ‚Äî routers call the same functions in `handlers/`.

```
handlers/getPurchases()  ‚Üê shared business logic
    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ routers/api/v1/purchases.ts  ‚Üê Hono .get("/purchases", ‚Ä¶)
```

When adding a resource, create the Hono router and a client module in `apps/frontend/src/lib/`.

### 4. Frontend calls API via `@costly/api-client` over HTTP

All client-side data fetching uses the typed Hono client with `credentials: 'include'`:

```
Route / useQuery / useMutation
  ‚Üí apps/frontend/src/lib/<resource>.ts
    ‚Üí apiClient.api.v1.* (HTTP to API worker)
      ‚Üí sessionMiddleware ‚Üí handlers/*.ts ‚Üí Drizzle
```

Auth uses `authClient` (better-auth) pointing at `VITE_API_URL/api/auth/*`.

### 5. Client-side data fetching with TanStack Query

Routes use `useQuery` / `useInfiniteQuery` / `useMutation` on the client. Route `beforeLoad` guards auth via `getSession()` from `auth-client`.

Mutations invalidate related query keys on success.

### 6. UI components from `@costly/components`

Use `@costly/components` for UI primitives and layouts. New custom components in the frontend use **Tailwind v3** (configured in `apps/frontend/tailwind.config.js` with the `@costly/components/tailwind-config` preset).

## Adding a New Resource (checklist)

1. **Schema** ‚Äî `apps/api/src/schema/<resource>.ts` + export from `index.ts`
2. **Handlers** ‚Äî `apps/api/src/handlers/<resource>.ts` (all Drizzle queries here)
3. **Hono router** ‚Äî `apps/api/src/routers/api/v1/<resource>.ts` + mount in `v1/index.ts`
4. **Client module** ‚Äî `apps/frontend/src/lib/<resource>.ts` using `createApiClientWithCredentials`
5. **Route** ‚Äî `apps/frontend/src/routes/...` with useQuery / useMutation pattern
6. **Export types** ‚Äî add to `apps/api/src/exports.ts` if needed by clients
